+# Research — meetings-workspace-detail-fix
+
+## Symptom (live-reproduced 2026-07-21 on locally-booted cxportal against staging DB)
+Admin Meetings Hub renders fine (3 seeded meetings). Clicking "Open workspace" on any
+meeting throws a Vite runtime overlay:
+
+```
+[plugin:runtime-error-plugin] Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'length')
+client/src/pages/meeting-workspace.tsx:846   {approvals.length === 0 ? (
+at MeetingApprovalsSection
+```
+
+## Evidence gathered
+- `client/src/pages/meeting-workspace.tsx:91-96` — `MeetingDetailResponse` declares
+  `{ meeting, contacts, comments, approvals }`.
+- `:1407` — `const { meeting, contacts, comments, approvals } = data;`
+- `:2036` — `<MeetingApprovalsSection approvals={approvals} />`; `:846` — `approvals.length`.
+- Query `:997` — `useQuery<MeetingDetailResponse>` against `meetingQueryKey`
+  (`/api/meetings/:id?orgId=`).
+- Server `server/routes.ts:3368` — `GET /api/meetings/:id` returns
+  `storage.getMeetingWithContacts(orgId, id)` unchanged.
+- Server `server/storage.ts:1880-1885` — `getMeetingWithContacts` returns ONLY
+  `{ meeting, contacts }`. No `comments`, no `approvals`.
+- Portal `server/routes.ts:7631-7648` — the portal detail endpoint already calls
+  `storage.getCommentsByMeeting(orgId, meetingId)` + `storage.getApprovalsByMeeting(orgId, meetingId)`.
+  Both helpers exist and are org-scoped.
+
+## Conclusion
+Data-shape mismatch: the admin detail endpoint under-delivers relative to the client
+contract. `comments`/`approvals` arrive `undefined`, so `.length` throws. Correct
+layer to fix is the server storage method (deliver the data the client already asks
+for), reusing the two org-scoped helpers the portal path already uses. No client
+change, no schema change.
+
+## Test gap
+Phase-1 tests exercised admin route status/org-scoping + portal render, never rendered
+`meeting-workspace.tsx` and never asserted the admin detail payload shape. Add a
+regression test on `GET /api/meetings/:id` asserting `comments` + `approvals` keys.
