+# OBF Master Plan — meetings-workspace-detail-fix
+
+## Problem (live-reproduced 2026-07-21)
+Clicking any meeting in the admin Meetings Hub crashes the workspace page with a runtime error at client/src/pages/meeting-workspace.tsx:846 where `approvals.length` is read on an undefined value inside MeetingApprovalsSection.
+
+## Root cause (verified in source)
+- Client `client/src/pages/meeting-workspace.tsx:91` types the detail query as `MeetingDetailResponse = { meeting, contacts, comments, approvals }` and at line 1407 destructures all four from `data`.
+- Server `GET /api/meetings/:id` (`server/routes.ts:3368`) returns `storage.getMeetingWithContacts(orgId, id)`.
+- `storage.getMeetingWithContacts` (`server/storage.ts:1880`) returns only `{ meeting, contacts }`. `comments` and `approvals` are therefore `undefined`, so `approvals.length` throws on every meeting open.
+- The portal endpoint `GET /api/portal/meetings/:id` (`server/routes.ts:7631`) already fetches both via `storage.getCommentsByMeeting` + `storage.getApprovalsByMeeting`. The admin detail path was simply never brought up to the same shape.
+
+## Why tests missed it
+Phase-1 tests exercised admin routes (status codes, org-scoping) and portal render, but never rendered `meeting-workspace.tsx`. No test asserted the admin detail payload shape includes `comments` + `approvals`.
+
+## Fix (server-side — the correct layer)
+Make the admin detail endpoint return the full shape the client already expects. Do NOT paper over it client-side with optional-chaining defaults — that would render the page but silently hide real approvals/comments. The data must actually be delivered.
+
+## Scope
+1 storage method + its interface signature + 1 regression test. No schema change, no client change (client type is already correct). Single repo. Qualifies as one-big-feature.
+
+## Verify
+- `npm run check` (tsc) clean.
+- `npm test` — new test asserts `GET /api/meetings/:id` returns `comments` + `approvals` arrays; existing meeting tests still green.
+- Larry live-clicks the full flow on a locally-booted instance against staging DB: hub, open meeting (no crash), comments section, approvals section, sign-off, portal view, PDF export.
