+# Spec 01 — Admin meeting-detail endpoint returns comments + approvals
+
+## Target files
+- `server/storage.ts` — `getMeetingWithContacts` (impl ~L1880, interface decl ~L493)
+- `tests/` — new/extended test for `GET /api/meetings/:id`
+
+## Exact change
+
+### 1. `server/storage.ts` — extend `getMeetingWithContacts`
+Return `comments` and `approvals` alongside `meeting` + `contacts`, reusing the existing storage helpers already used by the portal endpoint.
+
+Current impl:
+- fetches meeting via `this.getMeeting(orgId, id)`, returns undefined if missing
+- fetches contacts, returns `{ meeting, contacts }`
+
+New impl must additionally:
+- `const comments = await this.getCommentsByMeeting(orgId, id);`
+- `const approvals = await this.getApprovalsByMeeting(orgId, id);`
+- return `{ meeting, contacts, comments, approvals }`
+
+### 2. Update the interface signature (~L493)
+Match the new return type so the return object includes `comments` and `approvals` typed arrays.
+- Import the comment/approval row types if not already in scope. `getCommentsByMeeting` / `getApprovalsByMeeting` already return them, so infer the exact exported type names from those method signatures and reuse them — do not invent names.
+- Both helpers already exist and are org-scoped (used by the portal route). Reuse them verbatim — no new queries, no cross-org leak.
+
+## Constraints
+- No `any`. No `console.log`. Keep org-scoping (both helpers already take orgId).
+- No client change — `MeetingDetailResponse` already declares comments + approvals.
+- No schema/migration change.
+
+## Test (regression guard)
+Add a test that hits `GET /api/meetings/:id` for a seeded meeting and asserts the response body has `comments` (array) and `approvals` (array) keys, in addition to `meeting` + `contacts`. If an approval/comment is seeded, assert it appears. Follow the existing meetings test file's setup/harness pattern (find it under `tests/`).
+
+## Done when
+- `npm run check` gives 0 errors.
+- `npm test` gives new test green + existing meeting tests green.
